theorem Topology.frontier_diff_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    frontier (A \ B) ⊆ frontier A ∪ frontier B := by
  intro x hx
  -- Decompose the membership in the frontier of `A \ B`.
  rcases hx with ⟨hxClosDiff, hxNotIntDiff⟩
  -- Since `A \ B ⊆ A`, we already have `x ∈ closure A`.
  have hxClosA : x ∈ closure A := by
    have hSub : (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ A := fun y hy => hy.1
    exact (closure_mono hSub) hxClosDiff
  classical
  by_cases hIntA : x ∈ interior A
  · -- Case 1: `x ∈ interior A`
    -- We shall prove that `x ∈ frontier B`.
    -- First, show `x ∈ closure B`.
    have hxClosB : x ∈ closure B := by
      -- Use the neighbourhood characterization of the closure.
      refine (mem_closure_iff).2 ?_
      intro U hU hxU
      by_contra hDisjoint
      -- If `U ∩ B = ∅`, then the open set `U ∩ interior A`
      -- is contained in `A \ B`, contradicting `hxNotIntDiff`.
      have hUIA : IsOpen (U ∩ interior A) := hU.inter isOpen_interior
      have hxUIA : x ∈ U ∩ interior A := by
        exact ⟨hxU, hIntA⟩
      have hSub : (U ∩ interior A : Set X) ⊆ A \ B := by
        intro y hy
        have hAy : y ∈ A := interior_subset hy.2
        have hBy : y ∈ B := by
          have : y ∈ U ∩ B := by
            have : y ∈ U := hy.1
            have : y ∈ B := by
              have hContr : (U ∩ B : Set X).Nonempty := by
                by_contra h
                exact hDisjoint h
              rcases hContr with ⟨z, hz⟩
              exact (by
                have : z ∈ B := hz.2
                have : y = z := by
                  have : y ∈ U := hy.1
                  have : z ∈ U := hz.1
                  have : y = z := rfl
                  exact this
                simpa [this] using hz.2)
            exact this
          exact this.2
        exact ⟨hAy, by
          have : y ∈ B := hBy
          exact this⟩
      have hxIntDiff : x ∈ interior (A \ B) := by
        -- `U ∩ interior A` is an open neighbourhood of `x`
        -- contained in `A \ B`.
        refine (interior_maximal hSub hUIA) hxUIA
      exact hxNotIntDiff hxIntDiff
      -- Contradiction obtained, so `(U ∩ B).Nonempty`.
    -- Next, show `x ∉ interior B`.
    have hxNotIntB : x ∉ interior B := by
      intro hxIntB
      -- The open set `interior B` is disjoint from `A \ B`,
      -- contradicting the fact that `x ∈ closure (A \ B)`.
      have hNon :
          ((interior B : Set X) ∩ (A \ B)).Nonempty :=
        (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClosDiff (interior B) isOpen_interior hxIntB
      rcases hNon with ⟨y, hy⟩
      exact (hy.2.2 hy.2.2).elim
    -- Assemble the information to conclude `x ∈ frontier B`.
    have hxFrontB : x ∈ frontier B := And.intro hxClosB hxNotIntB
    exact Or.inr hxFrontB
  · -- Case 2: `x ∉ interior A`, hence `x ∈ frontier A`.
    have hxFrontA : x ∈ frontier A := And.intro hxClosA hIntA
    exact Or.inl hxFrontA

theorem Topology.frontier_closure_eq_closure_diff_interior_closure {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier (closure A) = closure A \ interior (closure A) := by
  simp [frontier, closure_closure]
